# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: CassiusFightsVaelen
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah walks up towards Cassius."
    new "Sarah walks up towards Cassius."

    old "I am still wounded from my fall."
    new "I am still wounded from my fall."

    old "Cassius looks at her."
    new "Cassius looks at her."

    old "I can see this."
    new "I can see this."

    old "Sarah knows he will want something in return."
    new "Sarah knows he will want something in return."

    old "I don't have it yet. The contract."
    new "I don't have it yet. The contract."

    old "His eyes remain fixed on hers."
    new "His eyes remain fixed on hers."

    old "But you will. Soon."
    new "But you will. Soon."

    old "But I cannot undo the contract now."
    new "But I cannot undo the contract now."

    old "Your word will be enough for me, should you give it."
    new "Your word will be enough for me, should you give it."

    old "Sarah saw the stern expression in Cassius' eyes."
    new "Sarah saw the stern expression in Cassius' eyes."

    old "I give you more word."
    new "I give you more word."

    old "Cassius bowed in turn."
    new "Cassius bowed in turn."

    old "Then I will be your champion."
    new "Then I will be your champion."

    old "Cassius...thank you."
    new "Cassius...thank you."

    old "She turned her head and looked at Vaelen."
    new "She turned her head and looked at Vaelen."

    old "I have fought besides him for years. He's a skilled fighter, but not without his flaws."
    new "I have fought besides him for years. He's a skilled fighter, but not without his flaws."

    old "A possible weakness you could exploit is-"
    new "A possible weakness you could exploit is-"

    old "Cassius threw up his hand and brought her to silence."
    new "Cassius threw up his hand and brought her to silence."

    old "Your counsel is appreciated, Sarah, but I will not have need of it."
    new "Your counsel is appreciated, Sarah, but I will not have need of it."

    old "Sarah watched as Cassius strode past her, out onto the open area which now had become like an arena."
    new "Sarah watched as Cassius strode past her, out onto the open area which now had become like an arena."

    old "The crowd seemed to react with excitement at Cassius' sudden appearance."
    new "The crowd seemed to react with excitement at Cassius' sudden appearance."

    old "Sarah looked at Dio."
    new "Sarah looked at Dio."

    old "Will your brother be alright?"
    new "Will your brother be alright?"

    old "I have worried on occasion for him. I do not worry now."
    new "I have worried on occasion for him. I do not worry now."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes towards the two men in the circle."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes towards the two men in the circle."

    old "This is what you send in your place, Sarah? A slave?"
    new "This is what you send in your place, Sarah? A slave?"

    old "You truly have no honour."
    new "You truly have no honour."

    old "Cassius stepped forward."
    new "Cassius stepped forward."

    old "You may call you Cassius, and I will serve as her champion, for she is too wounded to fight."
    new "You may call you Cassius, and I will serve as her champion, for she is too wounded to fight."

    old "Vaelen spat on the ground near Cassius."
    new "Vaelen spat on the ground near Cassius."

    old "She's a coward. And as for you...I'll call you whatever I want, slave."
    new "She's a coward. And as for you...I'll call you whatever I want, slave."

    old "Cassius only smiled, casually flexing his arms as if he was warming up."
    new "Cassius only smiled, casually flexing his arms as if he was warming up."

    old "You will call me Cassius, before this is over."
    new "You will call me Cassius, before this is over."

    old "Vaelen pulled his sword from the earth."
    new "Vaelen pulled his sword from the earth."

    old "Let us settle this!"
    new "Let us settle this!"

    old "He turned towards the crowd."
    new "He turned towards the crowd."

    old "Let all who bear witness today, know that this creature has been selected as Sarah Rose's champion."
    new "Let all who bear witness today, know that this creature has been selected as Sarah Rose's champion."

    old "And let it be known that when I break him, and I will break him, this matter will be settled in my favor."
    new "And let it be known that when I break him, and I will break him, this matter will be settled in my favor."

    old "As for Sarah herself, her fate will be exile."
    new "As for Sarah herself, her fate will be exile."

    old "Let her wander the earth as lost as the day I first found her. Stripped of all title or recognition. Nobody."
    new "Let her wander the earth as lost as the day I first found her. Stripped of all title or recognition. Nobody."

    old "Vaelen turned to Cassius."
    new "Vaelen turned to Cassius."

    old "Any last words, slave?"
    new "Any last words, slave?"

    old "Cassius smiled and spun around."
    new "Cassius smiled and spun around."

    old "He threw out his arms, as if putting his own body on display. His physique had been honed to perfection."
    new "He threw out his arms, as if putting his own body on display. His physique had been honed to perfection."

    old "I am a simple man. A slave, as some may call me."
    new "I am a simple man. A slave, as some may call me."

    old "So I will not bore you with a speech."
    new "So I will not bore you with a speech."

    old "Let it only be known that whatever honor I claim here today, I give in tribute to Sarah Rose."
    new "Let it only be known that whatever honor I claim here today, I give in tribute to Sarah Rose."

    old "I do not know all of you, but even in these few days I have learned how you have suffered under this man's foolishness."
    new "I do not know all of you, but even in these few days I have learned how you have suffered under this man's foolishness."

    old "It will be my pleasure to be not only Sarah's champion, but the people's champion as well."
    new "It will be my pleasure to be not only Sarah's champion, but the people's champion as well."

    old "Cassius threw up his hand and the crowd exploded into cheers."
    new "Cassius threw up his hand and the crowd exploded into cheers."

    old "Sarah could see that Vaelen was frustrated to hear his own men cheering against him."
    new "Sarah could see that Vaelen was frustrated to hear his own men cheering against him."

    old "Somehow, everyone knew the last of the words had been said on the matter."
    new "Somehow, everyone knew the last of the words had been said on the matter."

    old "Vaelen and Cassius drew into a fighting stance, raising up their weapons."
    new "Vaelen and Cassius drew into a fighting stance, raising up their weapons."

    old "A deathly silence descended on the crowd."
    new "A deathly silence descended on the crowd."

    old "Sarah watched as Vaelen began to carefully circle around Cassius."
    new "Sarah watched as Vaelen began to carefully circle around Cassius."

    old "As was Vaelen's way, he was looking for a weakness."
    new "As was Vaelen's way, he was looking for a weakness."

    old "Vaelen was a skill fighter in his own right. Not the greatst that the army had ever since, but certainly better than most."
    new "Vaelen was a skill fighter in his own right. Not the greatst that the army had ever since, but certainly better than most."

    old "His favored weapon, a large two-handed blade, was a weapon that over time he had learned to fire off like a cannon."
    new "His favored weapon, a large two-handed blade, was a weapon that over time he had learned to fire off like a cannon."

    old "Cassius for his part mirrored Vaelen's movement, circling in the opposite direction."
    new "Cassius for his part mirrored Vaelen's movement, circling in the opposite direction."

    old "Where Vaelen's movements were calculated, controlled, Cassius seemed at ease. Casual, almost."
    new "Where Vaelen's movements were calculated, controlled, Cassius seemed at ease. Casual, almost."

    old "Suddenly, Vaelen lunged forward."
    new "Suddenly, Vaelen lunged forward."

    old "He released the immense power in his arms and swung his great sword with surprising speed."
    new "He released the immense power in his arms and swung his great sword with surprising speed."

    old "The blade swung and cut only air."
    new "The blade swung and cut only air."

    old "Sarah wondered if her own eyes had cheated her."
    new "Sarah wondered if her own eyes had cheated her."

    old "Only a fraction before, Cassius had been there, but now the blade swung impotently through the air."
    new "Only a fraction before, Cassius had been there, but now the blade swung impotently through the air."

    old "Dirt was kicked up as Vaelen turned his body back to Cassius."
    new "Dirt was kicked up as Vaelen turned his body back to Cassius."

    old "Cassius, for his part, was only smiling."
    new "Cassius, for his part, was only smiling."

    old "He...dodged it?"
    new "He...dodged it?"

    old "I envy you, to watch Cassisu fight for the first time is always a delight."
    new "I envy you, to watch Cassisu fight for the first time is always a delight."

    old "Sarah could see Vaelen struggled with the same stunned surprise, but he tried to keep his face from revealing his feelings."
    new "Sarah could see Vaelen struggled with the same stunned surprise, but he tried to keep his face from revealing his feelings."

    old "Only because Sarah knew him well enough, could she see his doubt."
    new "Only because Sarah knew him well enough, could she see his doubt."

    old "Again, Vaelen lunged at Cassius, this time thrusting the blade forward."
    new "Again, Vaelen lunged at Cassius, this time thrusting the blade forward."

    old "A sickening crack rang out across the arena."
    new "A sickening crack rang out across the arena."

    old "Blood and broken teeth fell against the sand."
    new "Blood and broken teeth fell against the sand."

    old "Sarah watched Vaelen stumble forward, as stunned as everyone else."
    new "Sarah watched Vaelen stumble forward, as stunned as everyone else."

    old "Cassius had moved, impossibly fast as before, but rather than simply dodge, this time he had driven his shield into Vaelen's face."
    new "Cassius had moved, impossibly fast as before, but rather than simply dodge, this time he had driven his shield into Vaelen's face."

    old "When he pulled it back, the front of it was covered in blood and gore."
    new "When he pulled it back, the front of it was covered in blood and gore."

    old "Vaelen's face was a ruin."
    new "Vaelen's face was a ruin."

    old "The man who had barely suffered a wound for as long as he had been a mercenary, now felt his blood rushing out from his forehead."
    new "The man who had barely suffered a wound for as long as he had been a mercenary, now felt his blood rushing out from his forehead."

    old "There was so much of it."
    new "There was so much of it."

    old "Cassius easily spun around, holding the shield up like a prize."
    new "Cassius easily spun around, holding the shield up like a prize."

    old "The crowd went mad for him."
    new "The crowd went mad for him."

    old "As everyone looked at Cassius, Sarah saw Vaelen."
    new "As everyone looked at Cassius, Sarah saw Vaelen."

    old "Through the blood, she could see his furious eyes, but deeper still, a fear."
    new "Through the blood, she could see his furious eyes, but deeper still, a fear."

    old "The fear of a man who realized he was mortal."
    new "The fear of a man who realized he was mortal."

    old "Vaelen rushed towards Cassius who had his back turned to him."
    new "Vaelen rushed towards Cassius who had his back turned to him."

    old "But Cassius had eyes in the back of his head."
    new "But Cassius had eyes in the back of his head."

    old "Like a bullfighter, he spun his body and side-stepped Vaelen's blade."
    new "Like a bullfighter, he spun his body and side-stepped Vaelen's blade."

    old "Catching Vaelen as he stumbled by, Cassius grabbed Vaelen's wrist."
    new "Catching Vaelen as he stumbled by, Cassius grabbed Vaelen's wrist."

    old "Twisting, he spun Vaelen about and pinned him down against the ground."
    new "Twisting, he spun Vaelen about and pinned him down against the ground."

    old "A sound rang out, like a bundle of twigs, snapping."
    new "A sound rang out, like a bundle of twigs, snapping."

    old "Vaelen's blood curdled scream followed."
    new "Vaelen's blood curdled scream followed."

    old "Sarah saw his blade fall from his dominant hand, clattering against the earth."
    new "Sarah saw his blade fall from his dominant hand, clattering against the earth."

    old "The fight was over. Everyone, except perhaps Vaelen, knew it. It had barely been a fight."
    new "The fight was over. Everyone, except perhaps Vaelen, knew it. It had barely been a fight."

    old "Cassius turned his hand, twisting Vaelen's broken wrist, and keeping him pinned down."
    new "Cassius turned his hand, twisting Vaelen's broken wrist, and keeping him pinned down."

    old "With a sickening crunch, he brought his fist down on Vaelen's face, robbing him of what few teeth he had left."
    new "With a sickening crunch, he brought his fist down on Vaelen's face, robbing him of what few teeth he had left."

    old "Sarah knew it was Vaelen, but she could no longer recognize his face."
    new "Sarah knew it was Vaelen, but she could no longer recognize his face."

    old "Cassius kept his grip on Vaelen, still holding him down."
    new "Cassius kept his grip on Vaelen, still holding him down."

    old "So, do you yield?"
    new "So, do you yield?"

    old "Sarah could hear Vaelen mumble something, the blood drowning out his words."
    new "Sarah could hear Vaelen mumble something, the blood drowning out his words."

    old "Cassius turned to the crowd."
    new "Cassius turned to the crowd."

    old "Did any of you get that?"
    new "Did any of you get that?"

    old "The crowd laughed in the cruel way that only crowds could."
    new "The crowd laughed in the cruel way that only crowds could."

    old "More mumbled, drowned out words from Vaelen."
    new "More mumbled, drowned out words from Vaelen."

    old "Cassius leaned down to better hear him."
    new "Cassius leaned down to better hear him."

    old "Then, the glimmer of a blade in the sunlight."
    new "Then, the glimmer of a blade in the sunlight."

    old "Pulled from his boot, Vaelen shoved the dagger up to Cassius' neck."
    new "Pulled from his boot, Vaelen shoved the dagger up to Cassius' neck."

    old "Cassius was dead. If he had been any other man, he would have been dead."
    new "Cassius was dead. If he had been any other man, he would have been dead."

    old "Sarah watched as Cassius held Vaelen's other wrist in his hands, the blade only an inch away from his throat."
    new "Sarah watched as Cassius held Vaelen's other wrist in his hands, the blade only an inch away from his throat."

    old "Cassius roared with laughter, and the crowd joined him."
    new "Cassius roared with laughter, and the crowd joined him."

    old "Not only a fool, but a coward too!"
    new "Not only a fool, but a coward too!"

    old "This is your leader?"
    new "This is your leader?"

    old "This man who seeks to rob me of my victory by drawing daggers like some backalley cuthroat?"
    new "This man who seeks to rob me of my victory by drawing daggers like some backalley cuthroat?"

    old "Cassius leaned his knee further into Vaelen's back."
    new "Cassius leaned his knee further into Vaelen's back."

    old "With another sickening snap, he broke Vaelen's other wrist, the dagger clattering against the ground."
    new "With another sickening snap, he broke Vaelen's other wrist, the dagger clattering against the ground."

    old "I would have given you a soldier's death!"
    new "I would have given you a soldier's death!"

    old "But you are no soldier!"
    new "But you are no soldier!"

    old "Cassius released his grip on Vaelen."
    new "Cassius released his grip on Vaelen."

    old "Vaelen's broken arms fell besides him. There were no more tricks. No more words to be had."
    new "Vaelen's broken arms fell besides him. There were no more tricks. No more words to be had."

    old "Vaelen muttered something in stunned disbelief."
    new "Vaelen muttered something in stunned disbelief."

    old "Cassius brought the blade down with a lightning speed."
    new "Cassius brought the blade down with a lightning speed."

    old "Sarah saw more gore splatter out across the sand. She was happy that she didn't see all of it."
    new "Sarah saw more gore splatter out across the sand. She was happy that she didn't see all of it."

    old "Vaelen breathed out only blood; his broken head spilling something more of himself."
    new "Vaelen breathed out only blood; his broken head spilling something more of himself."

    old "The sand of the desert ate it all up."
    new "The sand of the desert ate it all up."

    old "Cassius threw up his bloodied fists, and the crowd roared with his name."
    new "Cassius threw up his bloodied fists, and the crowd roared with his name."

    old "The soldiers of the mercenary band, the gathered up scrap from all across the world, had not a mind for the nuances of slavery."
    new "The soldiers of the mercenary band, the gathered up scrap from all across the world, had not a mind for the nuances of slavery."

    old "But they understood power."
    new "But they understood power."

    old "And all could see that Cassius radiated with it."
    new "And all could see that Cassius radiated with it."

    old "From the side, Sarah could witness the nuanced play of power and influence. Status."
    new "From the side, Sarah could witness the nuanced play of power and influence. Status."

    old "How Cassius had seized on it and now loosely held it in his hand. He could claim so much for himself."
    new "How Cassius had seized on it and now loosely held it in his hand. He could claim so much for himself."

    old "Would he?"
    new "Would he?"

    old "Sarah had scarcely thought of it when she saw in his eyes that same recognition."
    new "Sarah had scarcely thought of it when she saw in his eyes that same recognition."

    old "Only, Cassius was less cynical than her, and never pretended to be other than he was."
    new "Only, Cassius was less cynical than her, and never pretended to be other than he was."

    old "She saw him twirl the glory in his hands and play to the crowd, enjoying it for a brief moment longer..."
    new "She saw him twirl the glory in his hands and play to the crowd, enjoying it for a brief moment longer..."

    old "Then he turned to her."
    new "Then he turned to her."

    old "Hands and body still bloodied with the gore of Vaelen, he strode across the sand."
    new "Hands and body still bloodied with the gore of Vaelen, he strode across the sand."

    old "He stopped before her, and the crowd, mesmerized, held their breath."
    new "He stopped before her, and the crowd, mesmerized, held their breath."

    old "Cassius fell to one knee and raised up a hand in supplication."
    new "Cassius fell to one knee and raised up a hand in supplication."

    old "Lady Sarah Rose..."
    new "Lady Sarah Rose..."

    old "He spoke the words clearly, and in the silence, all could hear him."
    new "He spoke the words clearly, and in the silence, all could hear him."

    old "I have won this victory, but I hold true to my word and dedicate all my glory to you."
    new "I have won this victory, but I hold true to my word and dedicate all my glory to you."

    old "I won in your name, and only in fighting for one as valiant as you, could I have gathered the strength and courage to win."
    new "I won in your name, and only in fighting for one as valiant as you, could I have gathered the strength and courage to win."

    old "Sarah watched his face move as she looked down on him."
    new "Sarah watched his face move as she looked down on him."

    old "He enjoyed the performance. The theatre. This was simply him playing to the crowd in a different way."
    new "He enjoyed the performance. The theatre. This was simply him playing to the crowd in a different way."

    old "She knew his skill was undeniable and that he would have called Vaelen in her name, or as casually as he would have killed any other."
    new "She knew his skill was undeniable and that he would have called Vaelen in her name, or as casually as he would have killed any other."

    old "But he pretended."
    new "But he pretended."

    old "He played the loyal servant, the faithful soldier."
    new "He played the loyal servant, the faithful soldier."

    old "Sarah extended one hand down, touching Cassius' forehead."
    new "Sarah extended one hand down, touching Cassius' forehead."

    old "Rise, Cassius."
    new "Rise, Cassius."

    old "A slave by circumstance, but a free man by valor. With all the Gods as my witness, and before all these men, I vow you will be free."
    new "A slave by circumstance, but a free man by valor. With all the Gods as my witness, and before all these men, I vow you will be free."

    old "She saw a smile on his face."
    new "She saw a smile on his face."

    old "And my sister too, he said without words."
    new "And my sister too, he said without words."

    old "Sarah gave a subtle nod."
    new "Sarah gave a subtle nod."

    old "And your sister too, she answered without words."
    new "And your sister too, she answered without words."

    old "The crowd exploded with more cheers, now rushing up towards each of them."
    new "The crowd exploded with more cheers, now rushing up towards each of them."

    old "Where before they chanted Cassius' name, they now also chanted Sarah's, and with each chant, her name grew louder."
    new "Where before they chanted Cassius' name, they now also chanted Sarah's, and with each chant, her name grew louder."

    old "Cassius easily slipped away into the crowd. He gotten what he wanted."
    new "Cassius easily slipped away into the crowd. He gotten what he wanted."

